{
  "doc_id": "48128",
  "text": "The similarity of the three-dimensional structures of SMN and SMNΔ7 shows that while there are profound functional significances, the minor sequence differences do not lead to a global disruption of SMN structure. The structures reported here demonstrate that SMNΔ7 is largely intact and therefore likely retains some (albeit, low) functional activity. This is consistent with in vivo activity of the SMNΔ7 protein in the transgenic mouse models in which over-expression of SMNΔ7 significantly extends survival and moderates a devastating phenotype [CITATION_1] . However, even massive levels of SMNΔ7 cannot fully rescue the SMA phenotype, demonstrating a critical role of the C-terminus region in the assembly process that cannot be efficiently accomplished by SMNΔ7 as its activity is associated with a significant reduction in snRNP assembly [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
